headline: Reassessing General Motors (GM) Valuation After Analyst Upgrades, Higher Guidance and New U.S. Investment
summary: General Motors (GM) just caught a wave of bullish attention, with several big banks upgrading the stock after the company boosted its earnings outlook and doubled down on U.S. factory investment. See our latest analysis for General Motors. The latest upgrades, higher earnings guidance, and fresh U.S. investment have clearly caught investors’ attention, with a roughly 57% year to date share price return and triple digit multi year total shareholder returns signaling that momentum is building...

headline: Looking at the Narrative for GM After Q3 Beat and Shifting Tariff Outlook
summary: General Motors stock has seen its fair value estimate nudged higher, rising from about $74.15 per share to roughly $76.12 as analysts reassess the company following a stronger than expected Q3 and raised guidance. With the discount rate steady at 12.5% and long term revenue growth assumptions ticking up slightly from around 1.19% to approximately 1.24%, the small upgrade reflects growing confidence in GM's ability to execute on cost controls, navigate tariffs, and sustain demand.
